We can simply use the approach for solving Coin Change II [#518](https://leetcode.com/problems/coin-change-2).
It only takes 5 lines without sorting at first.
```
class Solution:
    def combinationSum(self, candidates: List[int], target: int) -> List[List[int]]:
        dp = [[[]]] + [[] for _ in range(target)]
        for candidate in candidates:
            for i in range(candidate, target + 1):
                dp[i] += [sublist + [candidate] for sublist in dp[i - candidate]]
        return dp[target]
```
Time complexity O(length of candidates * target)
Space complexity O(target^3)

